text: I am working on an API and GET and POST are working fine except when I try and get a select record by its ID (e.g. /articles/2). The article exists and when retrieving all records via the /articles route I get a proper response. Here is the stack trace.
[GIN-debug] [WARNING] Running in "debug" mode. Switch to "release" mode in production.
2015/06/18 10:31:49 Panic recovery -> interface conversion: error is *errors.errorString, not *errors.Error
_, err := dbmap.Select(&articles, "select * from articles order by article_id")
err := dbmap.SelectOne(&article, "select * from articles where article_id=?", article_id)
